# 🛡️ DNIF Matrix-AI: Automated Support Plane

A localized, privacy-first Security Operations Center (SOC) Co-Pilot designed to automate context-aware client engagement responses for Jira tickets. This tool leverages an offline Mistral LLM to generate highly professional, template-driven responses without sending sensitive customer logs to external cloud APIs.

## ✨ Core Features
* **Offline AI Inference:** Runs entirely locally using Ollama and the Mistral 7B model, ensuring strict data privacy for security logs.
* **Real-Time Streaming:** Streams the LLM output directly to the UI using a custom FastAPI backend.
* **Prompt Template Architecture:** Configurable framing weights to adjust the tone and structure based on ticket classification (Case, Service Request, Feature Request).
* **Enterprise SOC Dashboard:** A premium, dark-mode cybersecurity user interface built with React and Tailwind CSS v4.

## 🛠️ Technology Stack
* **Frontend:** React, Vite, Tailwind CSS v4, Lucide Icons
* **Backend:** Python, FastAPI, Uvicorn, httpx
* **AI Engine:** Ollama (Local AI Runtime), Mistral-7B-Instruct

## 🚀 How to Run the Application
You will need three separate terminal instances running concurrently in your root directory to power the three layers of the application.

**Terminal 1: Start the AI Engine**
Keep the local AI server running in the background.
```bash
./bin/ollama serve

Terminal 2: Start the Python Backend
Activate the virtual environment and boot the FastAPI connector.

Bash
cd backend
source venv/bin/activate
uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8000
Terminal 3: Start the UI Dashboard
Launch the React frontend development server.

Bash
cd frontend
npm run dev
Access the application at: http://localhost:5173